<br>
Hermes skimmed slowly over the placid lake, glancing occasionally at his handsome and youthful appearance.  It felt great sheding his juvenile form and obtaining this more mature and masculine persona.  As he smiled to himself, lost in gentle thoughts, he suddenly became aware that he was once again close to civilization.<br>
<br>
&quot;Curses&quot; Hermes muttered to himself.  &quot;Is there no where I can go to without having to come up against mortals?&quot; <br>
<br>
He looked up, and scanned the horizan with immortal eyes, and realized that he was in a place filled with women.  Not a single male was present.  Searching mentally through his mind, he deduced that he had inadvertently happened upon an Amazon tribe.<br>
<br>
Curiosity nibbled at Hermes, and he decided to postpone his private sojourn, and instead detoured towards the tribe.  Invisible, and ephemeral, Hermes went in search of the Amazons.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen</span><br>  Posts: 175<br> <font color=#993300>(6/30/01 11:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=238.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Exploration</span><hr size=1>  The Amazon Assassin was curious, when her senses picked up on a male entering the lands of Themiscrya, and esepecially when she sensed the immortality. <br>
<br>
 Quickly Dawn had left her hut, climbed the nearest tree and began following her instinct. Dawn's hand grabbed onto the last tree branch, as she swung onto the next. <br>
<br>
 In a matter of minutes the Amazon had made it to the lake, but she didn't make herself known. The assassin figured if he was a god, he would sense her. Most likely sense her long before she had gotten there. <br>
<br>
 Therefore, she just settled atop the tree branch, observing. <p>Pyschotic injustice
