<br>
Before approaching shore, he had noticed several well camouflaged rafts docked near by.  Hermes decided that that would be a great place to start.  He reached the rafts, and gently removed the covering of leaves and branches.<br>
<br>
These were expertly crafted, Hermes thought, as he ran his fingers over the hull of the craft.  Strong hands were at work here, each carving was done with focus and precision.  Hermes respect for these women increased as he realized that there were many male civilizations whose claim to fame could never reach that of this female tribe.<br>
<br>
Smiling to himself, Hermes began to walk into the forest.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#993300>(7/1/01 3:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=238.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Unwary</span><hr size=1>  There was a soft growl as the amazon watched the god inspect their rafts, but then it stopped. Dawn was realizing how much respect he held.. and she was very surprised. <br>
<br>
 As he entered the forest, Dawn followed by tree top. She was stealthy in the trees as were the others. Unless she made a wrong move the god wouldn't find her. The amazon would make herself shown..in due time. <p>Pyschotic injustice
