Her golden eyes stayed put upon Hermes.  As she slinked along the forest floor, her muscles were tense.  Even though she was watching Hermes, it was not he who she was hunting.  But, if she was lucky.  He would take her to the prey she sought. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/umeihao.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Meihao</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#993300>(7/1/01 5:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=238.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Let the fun begin</span><hr size=1> Hermes smiled to himself.  He had made the mistake of assuming that he was just entering into another land which contained the run-of-the-mill type of people.  But he had caught himself before committing the error even further.  These are not normal women, but women of exceptional strength and skill.<br>
<br>
The fact that he hadn't seen any of them, and the fact that none had approached him, only strengthened his admiration for these warriors.  He had unwittingly become the prey it seemed.<br>
<br>
Not wanting to antagonize the Amazons, but also not wanting to appear foolish and weak, he realized that he had to keep going.  If he left now, he would be thought of as a coward, and he knew cowardice was not part of the Amazon vocabulary.<br>
<br>
Not knowing who or whom was hunting him, he decided to have a little fun with these warriors.  Wanting the hunt to be fair yet a bit challenging, Hermes nonchalantly walked into and merged with a nearby oak tree.  And down the trail, from ten different trees emerged ten identical Hermes each heading in a random direction.  <br>
<br>
::Let the fun begin.<br>
