But, she also did not want him.  Only to follow. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> Meihao</span><br> <span class=usertitle>Unregistered User</span><br>   <font color=#993300>(7/1/01 7:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=238.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Trouble</span><hr size=1> Hermes turned around when he heard the challenge.  What had meant to be a test of skills had somehow turned awry.  He knew he didn't have much time, because these warriors were protected by their goddess, Artemis.  And he felt Artemis would not think too highly of having someone, even her own kin, trespass against her people.<br>
<br>
Realizing the game had suddenly increased a few notches in stake, he quickly increased his senses.  Having never come across any of these people, he didn't know what they would do or be capable of doing.  As his senses spread out like wavefronts before him, he realized something was strangely amiss.<br>
<br>
Another immortal was in this vicinity.  Someone that had the tang of blood.  Also, the scent wasn't that of a Greek Olympian, but Sumerian?  Interesting.  But why here, and why now?<br>
<br>
Not wanting to be caught in a trap by either predator, Hermes went into action.  All ten Hermes took flight.  Three lept into the foliage above, immediately hidden by the dense foliage.  Two ran back into the trees with which they had appeared.  One melded into the ground below, while the other four faded with the wind.  <br>
<br>
Hermes had wanted to step into a rift and be somewhere else.  He hadn't realized that his playful nature had infuriated the Amazons.  And since it was his fault, it wouldn't be right to go on the offensive first.  Plus he realized he couldn't leave that easily, someone or something was preventing his departure.  Was it his sister, the Sumerian, the Amazons, or some other factor?He realized his sidetrip had suddenly become deadly.<br>
