The familiar decided to leave the two and move north.  Something was up north that she needed to seek out.  Muscles flexed and the lioness slipped away in the thick air of the forests, bounding thru the trees once away from Dawn and Hermes.  Her excitement growing. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/udawnithinia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dawnithinia </A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen</span><br>  Posts: 189<br> <font color=#993300>(7/2/01 8:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=238.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Introductions.. whee fun.</span><hr size=1>  The sword was flipped one last time in the palm of the assassin, and then sheathed at her side. Emeralds watching Hermes cautiously.<br>
<br>
 &quot;You got off on the wrong foot coming into these lands without invitation, and without telling anyone. You are never alone in the Amazon Forests.. remember that. And now please leave.. or ask permission from Queen Hippolyte next time.&quot;<br>
<br>
 There was an angry growl, and then Dawn turned, dissappearing into a tree. But not completely..she would remain to watch. <p>Pyschotic injustice
