In a bright flash and the sound of peacocks, Hera appeared before Hermes.  Her icy blue eyes narrowed at the new God.<br>
&quot;So, this is Hermes.....Zeus's new little Olympian,&quot; as she spoke a dark laugh arose. &quot;And so brave...to leave his mother's side so soon. Tell me are you as fast as they say, boy?&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uo0ohestiao0o.showPublicProfile?language=EN>o0o hestia o0o</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#993300>(7/3/01 9:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=238.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: So this is Hermes</span><hr size=1> ~Hestia appeared at Hermes side again when she heard her sister's appearence~<br>
